          <msContents>
            <summary>Collection of praises and hymns (stotras), Tantric rites and mantras, descriptions of diagrams (yantras) for use in worship (pūjā), mantras for the removal of curses (śapoddhāra), etc.; primarily dedicated to Hindu goddesses especially the goddess Lakṣmī and Candi to whom the manuscript is dedicated (f. 1v); contents include the Puṭkaraṇapryoga and the Saptaśatiprayoga.</summary>
